ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: The event name for which the data was collected
First day of (expected) wear of 3 week protocol
Week number starting from first day of protocol wear
0=weekdays only, 1=weekend only, 2=weekday and weekend
Average number of minutes of wear not excluded or considered sleep (by 60 second sleep record)
Notes: Individual day only included if day minutes >599

ElementDescription: Average number of minutes of wear considered sleep (by 60 second sleep record) not excluded due to HR quality checks
Notes: Individual day only included if day minutes >599

ElementDescription: Sum of steps during day_min on included days
Notes: Individual day only included if day minutes >599

ElementDescription: Sum of minutes spent in sedentary (<1.5 METS) activity during day_min on included days
Notes: Individual day only included if day minutes >599

ElementDescription: Sum of minutes spent in light (1.5-2.9METS) activity during day_min on included days
Notes: Individual day only included if day minutes >599

ElementDescription: Sum of minutes spent in moderate (3-5.9 METS) activity during day_min on included days
Notes: Individual day only included if day minutes >599

ElementDescription: Sum of of minutes spent in vigorous (6+ METS) activity during day_min on included days
Notes: Individual day only included if day minutes >599

ElementDescription: Average number of daily steps during day_min during included days
Notes: Individual day only included if day minutes >599

ElementDescription: Average METS/min during day_min on included days
Notes: Individual day only included if day minutes >599

ElementDescription: Average minutes spent in sedentary (<1.5 METS) activity during day_min on included days
Notes: Individual day only included if day minutes >599

ElementDescription: Average minutes spent in light (1.5-2.9METS) activity during day_min on included days
Notes: Individual day only included if day minutes >599

ElementDescription: Average minutes spent in moderate (3-5.9 METS) activity during day_min on included days
Notes: Individual day only included if day minutes >599

ElementDescription: Average minutes spent in vigorous (>6 METS) activity during day_min on included days
Notes: Individual day only included if day minutes >599

ElementDescription: Average resting heart rate from all included days from the daily level fitbit record
Notes: Low(er) resting heart rate is usually indicative of a) stronger cardiac muscle/better cardiorespiratory fitness and b) improved (para)sympathetic nervous tone

ElementDescription: Number of weekend days included in averages
Notes: Individual day only included if day minutes >599

ElementDescription: Number of weekdays included in averages
Notes: Individual day only included if day minutes >599

ElementDescription: 0=no, 1=yes.  ABCD inclusion rule is minimum of 4 days, 1 of which must be a weekend day
Notes: Individual day only included if day minutes >599

ElementDescription: Number of steps per day according to fitbit daily level summary
Notes: Individual day only included if day minutes >599 based upon ABCD QC record

ElementDescription: Average minutes spent in sedentary (<1.5 METS) activity during day_min on included days based upon daily level fitbit record
Notes: Individual day only included if day minutes >599 based upon ABCD QC record

ElementDescription: Average minutes spent in light (1.5-2.9METS) activity during day_min on included days based upon daily level fitbit record
Notes: Individual day only included if day minutes >599 based upon ABCD QC record

ElementDescription: Average minutes spent in moderate (3-5.9 METS) activity during day_min on included days based upon daily level fitbit record
Notes: Individual day only included if day minutes >599 based upon ABCD QC record

ElementDescription: Average minutes spent in vigorous (6+ METS) activity during day_min on included days based upon daily level fitbit record
Notes: Individual day only included if day minutes >599 based upon ABCD QC record
